name: United States v. Yazell
question: Does Federal or local Texas law apply to the loan?

name: Kent v. United States
question: Was the juvenile court's waiver of jurisdiction valid?
description: A case in which the Court held that proper investigation is necessary before a waive of jurisdiction by a juvenile court.

name: Graham v. John Deere Company of Kansas City
question: Did the Patent Act of 1952 codify the judicial test of obviousness, adding it to the statutory requirements of novelty and utility for the patentability of an invention? Did the Act change the general level required for the patentability of an invention?

name: Federal Trade Commission v. Brown Shoe Company, Inc.
Western Pacific Railroad Company v. United States
Jones & Laughlin Steel Corporation v. Gridiron Steel Company
Fairfax Family Fund, Inc. v. California
Walker Process Equipment, Inc. v. Food Machinery & Chemical Corporation
Interstate Commerce Commission v. Atlantic Coast Line Railroad Company
First Security National Bank & Trust Co of Lexington v. United States
Federal Trade Commission v. Mary Carter Paint Company
International Union, United Automobile, Aerospace & Agricultural Implement Workers of America, AFL-CIO, Local 283 v. Scofield
United Steelworkers of America v. R. H. Bouligny, Inc.
United States v. Romano
question: Did Romano and Ottiano's presence at the illegal operation in and of itself justify their convictions for possession? If jury instruction was invalid, is that sufficient to invalidate the charges for possession?

name: Carnation Company v. Pacific Westbound Conference
United Gas Improvement Company v. Callery Properties, Inc.
Time, Inc. v. Hill
question: Is a publication, containing misrepresentations about the subject of its coverage, protected under the First Amendment's freedom of speech guarantees?

name: South Carolina v. Katzenbach
question: Did the Act violate the states' rights to implement and control elections?
description: A case in which the Court held that the Fifteenth Amendment is a valid constitutional basis for the Voting Rights Act of 1965.

name: Fribourg Navigation Company, Inc. v. Commissioner
United Mine Workers of America v. Gibbs
Gunther v. San Diego & Arizona Eastern Railway Company
United States v. Ewell
question: Does the Sixth Amendment’s right to a speedy trial require dismissal of the new indictments?
description: A case in which the Court the Sixth Amendment’s right to a speedy trial did not requires dismissal of indictments against Ewell et al.

name: United States v. Standard Oil Company
question: Does the Rivers and Harbors Act prohibiting the discharge of “any refuse matter of any kind or description” into navigable waters cover commercially valuable aviation gasoline?

name: Albertson v. Subversive Activities Control Board
question: Did the member registration requirements of the Subversive Activities Control Act violate Albertson's and Proctor’s Fifth Amendment privileges against self-incrimination?

name: Idaho Sheet Metal Works, Inc. v. Wirtz
United States v. Von's Grocery Company
Wallis v. Pan American Petroleum Corporation
Maryland ex rel. Levin v. United States
A Book Named "John Cleland's Memoirs of a Woman of Pleasure" v. Attorney General of Massachusetts
question: Did the actions of Massachusetts violate the First Amendment?

name: Pennsylvania Public Utility Commission v. Pennsylvania Railroad Company
Rosenblatt v. Baer
question: Does a government official have to prove that defamatory statements were made in actual malice to succeed in a libel action?
description: A case in which the Court held that a government official has to prove that defamatory statements were made in actual malice to succeed in a libel action.

name: International Union, United Automobile, Aerospace & Agricultural Implement Workers of America (UAW), AFL-CIO v. Hoosier Cardinal Corporation
DeGregory v. Attorney General of New Hampshire
Leh v. General Petroleum Corporation
question: Is Leh's claim similar enough to that made by the government in Standard Oil to justify his use of collateral estoppel? Was Leh's claim valid because the Clayton Act suspended the running of the statute of limitations?

name: United States v. Pabst Brewing Company
Brown v. Louisiana
question: Did the actions of the arresting officer infringe upon Brown's (and his companions') freedom of speech, assembly, and freedom to petition the Government for redress of grievances as protected by the First and Fourteenth Amendments?

name: Bradley v. School Board of City of Richmond
Ginzburg v. United States
question: Does conviction under the federal obscenity statute, for pandering advertisements for sexually explicit publications, violate of the First Amendment's free speech protections if the advertisements are not themselves obscene?

name: Richmond Television Corporation v. United States
Seaboard Air Line Railroad Company v. United States
United States v. Anthony Grace & Sons, Inc.
United States v. Utah Construction & Mining Company
Linn v. United Plant Guard Workers
United States v. General Motors Corporation
Harper v. Virginia Board of Elections
question: Did the Virginia poll tax violate the Equal Protection Clause of the Fourteenth Amendment?
description: A case in which the Court held the Virginia poll tax violated the Equal Protection Clause.

name: Mishkin v. New York
question:
1. Was New York’s anti-obscenity statute impermissibly vague?
  2. Were Mishkin’s books properly found to be obscene?
  3. Must the government show that Mishkin knew the books were obscene?

name: Sheppard v. Maxwell
question: What threshold must be crossed before a trial is said to be so prejudicial, due to context and publicity, as to interfere with a defendant's Fifth Amendment due process right to a fair trial?
description: A case in which the Court held that the media coverage of a trial may have altered the jurors' views, thus denying the defendant a fair trial.

name: Shuttlesworth v. City of Birmingham
question:
(1) Is an ordinance making it an offense to stand, loiter or walk on any city sidewalk in a way that obstructs others’ free passage over that sidewalk unconstitutional as applied to Shuttlesworth?

(2) Is an ordinance making it an offense to stand or loiter on a city sidewalk after a request by a policeman to “move on” unconstitutional as applied to Shuttlesworth?

name: Dennis v. United States
question: 1. Does the indictment charge a conspiracy to defraud the United States Government consistent with 18 U.S.C. 371? 2. Is section 9(h) of the Taft- Hartley Act a bill of attainder in violation of Article I, Section 9, Clause 3 of the U.S. Constitution? 3. Did the trial court err in denying the defense's request for access to grand jury testimony of prosecution witnesses or in camera inspection of the testimony?
description: A case in which the Court held that the arrest of members of the Communist Party of America for violation of the Smith Act did not infringe upon the member's First Amendment rights.

name: Tehan v. United States ex rel. Shott
United States v. Maryland ex rel. Meyer
Joseph E. Seagram & Sons, Inc. v. Hostetter
United States v. Price
question: Did Price and the other defendants violate federal law when they murdered three men on June 21, 1964?
description: A case in which the Court held that Price and the other defendants violate federal law when they murdered three men on June 21, 1964.

name: Koehring Company v. Hyde Construction Company, Inc.
Harris v. United States
question: Is Harris guilty of criminal contempt under Federal Rule of Criminal Procedure 42(a)?

name: Evans v. Newton
question: When private actors fulfill public or governmental duties, are they subject to constitutional restrictions?
description: A case in which the Court held that a private park operator is subject to the Fourteenth Amendment if the park is municipal in character.

name: Securities and Exchange Commission v. New England Electric System
United States v. Equitable Life Assurance Soc. of United States
United States v. Guest
question: Was the federal indictment based on an offense under the laws of the United States?
description: A case in which the Court held that if a state participates at all in a conspiracy affecting an individual's right of free interstate passage, it has violated the Fourteenth Amendment with regard to any individuals whose rights are infringed, based on the constitutional right to travel.

name: Schmerber v. California
question: Did the blood test violate the Fifth Amendment guarantee against self-incrimination?

name: Brotherhood of Locomotive Engineers v. Chicago, Rock Island & Pacific Railroad Company
Hanna Mining Company v. District 2, Marine Engineers Beneficial Association, AFL-CIO
question: Does the NLRA preempt the state's authority to enjoin a marine engineer union's picketing where the marine engineers are defined as supervisors and not employees?

name: Brotherhood of Railway & Steamship Clerks, Freight Handlers, Express & Station Employees, AFL-CIO v. Florida East Coast Railway Company
Miranda v. Arizona
question: Does the Fifth Amendment’s protection against self-incrimination extend to the police interrogation of a suspect?
description: A case in which the Court held that law enforcement cannot use testimony given by anyone under interrogation while in custody without that person being informed of their legal rights.

name: United States v. Huck Manufacturing Co.
question:
(1) Should the Court overrule United States v. General Electric Co. which held that a license to make a patented article on the condition that the licensee sell the articles at a price set by the patent holder was illegal?

(2) If not, does a patent holder's decision not to grant additional licenses, as long as the first licensee sells the product at a price set by the patent holder, violate the Sherman Act?

name: Katzenbach v. Morgan
question: Does Section 4(e) of the Voting Rights Act of 1965 exceed the scope of Congress' powers to enact legislation because it infringes on powers reserved to the states under the Tenth Amendment?

name: Clayton Chemical & Packaging Company v. United States
Gondeck v. Pan American World Airways, Inc.
Federal Trade Commission v. Dean Foods Company
Albanese v. N. V. Nederl. Amerik Maats.
